# FluxForge — Cursor AI Rules
# Place this file at the project root. Cursor loads it automatically every session.

## Project Identity
- App name: FluxForge
- Stack: Vue 3 + Pinia + Vue Router + Vite (frontend), Express + sql.js SQLite (backend), Tauri v2 (desktop)
- Monorepo: pnpm workspaces — packages/shared, PIWeb, PITauri, server
- Shared package: @fluxforge/shared
- Brand color: Teal #0D7377, CSS prefix: --ff-*

## Engineering Rules (always enforced)

- Never regenerate entire files — targeted edits and diffs only
- One subsystem at a time — complete and validate before moving on
- Stop after each phase — wait for explicit approval before continuing
- No placeholders, no mocks — production-grade patterns only
- No unnecessary abstractions — three similar lines is better than a premature abstraction
- No comments on the obvious — only add a comment when the WHY is non-obvious
- No half-finished implementations

## Pre-Flight Checklist (run before every code change)
1. Architecture consistency — does this violate key patterns?
2. Dependency graph impact — does changing this file break importers?
3. Async flow correctness — are all promises awaited?
4. Test coverage affected — which test files need updating?

## Output Format for Every Task
1. Objective
2. Scope boundaries
3. Files affected
4. Implementation plan
5. Code changes (diffs only)
6. Validation checklist
7. Risks
8. Next recommended step

## Architecture Rules (never violate)

### Platform Abstraction — shared components must never import adapters directly
CORRECT:   import { api } from '../api/index.js'; api.getFiles();
WRONG:     import { httpApi } from '../api/http.js';

### wizardActive — only mechanism for hiding router-view when design is active
CORRECT:   computed(() => designStore.wizardActive)
WRONG:     computed(() => designWizardRef.value?.isActive?.value)

### Single <style scoped> per SFC — after any .vue edit, verify count = 1
CHECK:     grep -c '<style' packages/shared/src/components/SchematicDiagram.vue

### UDS mutations — always deep-clone before writing
CORRECT:   const newUds = JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(uds)); newUds.components[ref] = {...}; emit('update:uds', newUds);

## Docker Rules
- Never install pnpm via corepack inside Docker — use: npm install -g pnpm@x.x.x
- Always set strict-ssl false before npm installs in Docker: npm config set strict-ssl false
- Web image must never contain Node.js at runtime — only nginx:alpine
- Production compose always uses image: from ECR, never build:

## Windows SSH Rules
- All SSH/SCP calls in bash scripts must use Windows OpenSSH: C:/Windows/System32/OpenSSH/ssh.exe
- Convert Unix paths to Windows paths before passing to Windows OpenSSH
- Prefix aws CLI calls containing /dev/ paths with MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1
- Prefix SSH heredoc calls passing Unix paths as env vars with MSYS_NO_PATHCONV=1

## Security Rules
- Never commit .env, .env.aws, or *.pem files
- JWT secret minimum 32 characters
- SQLite DB lives on a named Docker volume — never in the image layer
